dAQDYKuwTv6CxvoxoWwRxub8XAQzkeUpylc8wtCLTd4rv5EB-CaPuJuUc5lRlyEVIn4347QB13tvPm0kjP1--H8DNh7otmC4Mcc8Ix0NpvT3HBZEyT4JZkeBRpf8lQmcR6N2_RFwy2QPB6MxaP9cLJvh9wN8zETmAzhP2oivnkFA07Knyxj3Wri8MTAgqaZP9vVwWr7EMC91vTzYMfyVNLelZOU-gcwCsAgXBHbH8iUIfcRcTgro1SZRGjdJfB9MlKoG8utCQiklZYLx2VHr3fGs-8aeNJSRqZ5A5JdZaifIyd-RKAR9_O7eeFWhPTzCtm9MipQ0nItD3YJJqr-PVrUeWRp_pyKohZT3s=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering SLF4J Logging**\\n\\nI’m thinking about whether I should add a fake SLF4J backend. The build.gradle might be too complicated. It seems I need to avoid retesting existing classes or logic flows, and direct logger use isn't an option. I’m considering a potential test using SLF4J LogMarker with an import and some assertions around markers. I want to ensure the logger's functionality, but it appears I won't be testing the Slf4jLogger's markerIfPresent. I need more clarity on the Akka Logging marker API.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Logging in Akka**\\n\\nI'm looking at the Akka 2.6 docs regarding LogMarker usage. The LoggingAdapter has methods for various log levels where I can use markers for logging. Since ActorLogging implements the LoggingAdapter, I could introduce a new actor message to log with `Slf4jLogMarker`. However, I need to adhere to the guidelines about not modifying existing logic. While adding new cases seems harmless, I’m hesitant since logging has already been tested, and this could introduce redundancy. I need to think this through more carefully.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating logging updates**\\n\\nI notice that the logging system doesn't currently cover any markers, which feels like a gap. I'm thinking about how this new marker flow on LoggingAdapter could really help improve clarity and tracking. It seems that addressing this might offer better insights into the logging process. I'm curious about how this can work in practice and what benefits it might bring in improving system performance and debugging. There’s a lot of potential here!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_IBbFMBoAfyrYzPxwuU4Ue38v|fc_0ce37203789b38590169fabeb7469c81a2ae856eb9b8af854e", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.typesafe.akka/akka-slf4j_2.13/2.6.21/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_akka/akka_slf4j_2_13/Akka_slf4j_2_13Test.scala", "edits": [{"oldText": "import akka.event.slf4j.{Logger => Slf4jEventLogger}\nimport org.slf4j.MDC\n", "newText": "import akka.event.slf4j.{Logger => Slf4jEventLogger, Slf4jLogMarker}\nimport org.slf4j.MDC\nimport org.slf4j.MarkerFactory\n"}, {"oldText": "  @Test\n  def configuredSlf4jLoggerHandlesErrorsWithoutStoppingTheActor(): Unit = {\n    withActorSystem(\"Slf4jErrorLoggingTest\") { system =>\n      implicit val timeout: Timeout = Timeout(RequestTimeout)\n      val logger = system.actorOf(Props(new EventStreamLoggingActor), \"error-logger\")\n\n      val afterFailure = Await.result(logger ? EventStreamLoggingActor.LogFailureAndAck(\"charlie\"), RequestTimeout)\n      val afterRecovery = Await.result(logger ? EventStreamLoggingActor.LogAndAck(\"delta\"), RequestTimeout)\n\n      assertThat(afterFailure).isEqualTo(EventStreamLoggingActor.Ack(\"failure\", \"charlie\"))\n      assertThat(afterRecovery).isEqualTo(EventStreamLoggingActor.Ack(\"event-stream\", \"delta\"))\n    }\n  }\n", "newText": "  @Test\n  def configuredSlf4jLoggerHandlesErrorsWithoutStoppingTheActor(): Unit = {\n    withActorSystem(\"Slf4jErrorLoggingTest\") { system =>\n      implicit val timeout: Timeout = Timeout(RequestTimeout)\n      val logger = system.actorOf(Props(new EventStreamLoggingActor), \"error-logger\")\n\n      val afterFailure = Await.result(logger ? EventStreamLoggingActor.LogFailureAndAck(\"charlie\"), RequestTimeout)\n      val afterRecovery = Await.result(logger ? EventStreamLoggingActor.LogAndAck(\"delta\"), RequestTimeout)\n\n      assertThat(afterFailure).isEqualTo(EventStreamLoggingActor.Ack(\"failure\", \"charlie\"))\n      assertThat(afterRecovery).isEqualTo(EventStreamLoggingActor.Ack(\"event-stream\", \"delta\"))\n    }\n  }\n\n  @Test\n  def loggingAdapterAcceptsSlf4jMarkersForMarkedEvents(): Unit = {\n    withActorSystem(\"Slf4jMarkerLoggingTest\") { system =>\n      val logger = akka.event.Logging(system, getClass)\n      val slf4jMarker = MarkerFactory.getMarker(\"akka-slf4j-marked-event\")\n      val marker = Slf4jLogMarker(slf4jMarker)\n\n      logger.debug(marker, \"debug message with slf4j marker\")\n      logger.info(marker, \"info message with slf4j marker\")\n      logger.warning(marker, \"warning message with slf4j marker\")\n      logger.error(marker, new RuntimeException(\"marked adapter failure\"), \"error message with slf4j marker\")\n\n      assertThat(marker.name).isEqualTo(slf4jMarker.getName)\n      assertThat(marker.marker()).isSameAs(slf4jMarker)\n    }\n  }\n"}]}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/com.typesafe.akka/akka-slf4j_2.13/2.6.21/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_akka/akka_slf4j_2_13/Akka_slf4j_2_13Test.scala\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"import akka.event.slf4j.{Logger => Slf4jEventLogger}\\nimport org.slf4j.MDC\\n\",\"newText\":\"import akka.event.slf4j.{Logger => Slf4jEventLogger, Slf4jLogMarker}\\nimport org.slf4j.MDC\\nimport org.slf4j.MarkerFactory\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"  @Test\\n  def configuredSlf4jLoggerHandlesErrorsWithoutStoppingTheActor(): Unit = {\\n    withActorSystem(\\\"Slf4jErrorLoggingTest\\\") { system =>\\n      implicit val timeout: Timeout = Timeout(RequestTimeout)\\n      val logger = system.actorOf(Props(new EventStreamLoggingActor), \\\"error-logger\\\")\\n\\n      val afterFailure = Await.result(logger ? EventStreamLoggingActor.LogFailureAndAck(\\\"charlie\\\"), RequestTimeout)\\n      val afterRecovery = Await.result(logger ? EventStreamLoggingActor.LogAndAck(\\\"delta\\\"), RequestTimeout)\\n\\n      assertThat(afterFailure).isEqualTo(EventStreamLoggingActor.Ack(\\\"failure\\\", \\\"charlie\\\"))\\n      assertThat(afterRecovery).isEqual